# RTK shell commands

When running commands via the Shell tool, **always prefix with `rtk`** for supported CLI tools. Do not rely on the Cursor preToolUse hook — call RTK explicitly.

## Examples

```bash
# Good
rtk git status
cd /path/to/repo && rtk git diff
rtk ls -la

# Bad
git status
```

## Compound commands

Apply `rtk` to each rewritable subcommand:

```bash
cd /Users/zalvey/Documents/animalDoku && rtk git status
```

## Exceptions

- RTK meta commands: `rtk gain`, `rtk hook check`, `rtk proxy` (use as documented)
- Commands with no RTK wrapper (e.g. `xcodebuild`, `swift`): run directly, or use `rtk proxy '<full command>'` when raw output is needed

## Verify rewrites

```bash
rtk hook check --agent cursor "git status"
```
